|author=Waterer GW, Robertson H
|pmid=19144044
|doi=10.1111/j.1440-1843.2008.01446.x
}}</ref>  Other rare causes of ILI include [[leukemia]] and [[metal fume fever]].

==In horses==
ILI occurs in some horses after [[intramuscular injection]] of [[vaccine]]s.  For these horses, light exercise speeds resolution of the ILI.  [[Non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug]]s (NSAIDs) may be given with the vaccine.<ref>{{cite book
|title=All horse systems go : the horse owner's full-color veterinary care and conditioning resource for modern performance, sport, and pleasure horses
|author=Loving, Nancy S
|year=2006
|publisher=Trafalger Square Publishing
|oclc=61864306}} page 439</ref>

==In ice hockey==
In the sport of [[ice hockey]], the term "flu-like symptoms" has been used in injury reports to hide the fact  from opposing teams that a player actually has a slight [[concussion]] instead. {{citationneeded|date=March 2013}}

